    fix(can): restore MCP2518FD interrupt + on-demand enable on JP7.2
    
    CAN (can0/can1) was completely dead on JP7.2. Two root causes:
    
    - pinmux: JP7.2's regenerated MB1 BCT flipped nvidia,enable-input from
      ENABLE (7.1) to DISABLE on the CAN INT pins (soc_gpio21_pdd3 /
      soc_gpio22_pdd4); the SoC never senses the line so the IRQ never fires.
      Restored to ENABLE (requires bootloader/BCT reflash).
    - the INT line is held LOW (not a real idle-high INT) -> the level-low IRQ
      storms and gets spurious-disabled, and self-start is flaky on the R39
      kernel. can_enable.sh nudges the GPIO interrupt-enable bit until genirq
      settles it into poll mode.
    
    can_enable.sh is seeded via rootfs /etc/skel (auto-installed to
    /home/mic-741). CAN is OFF by default for AD safety; enable on demand
    with: sudo ~/can_enable.sh. See docs/can-bus-pinmux-interrupt.md.

